      "target": {
        "kind": "issue",
        "state": "open",
        "locked": false,
        "title": "Surface Slack external arg-menu fallback as a visible health signal",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nIn `src/slack/monitor/slash.ts`, failures during external arg-menu registration are treated as best-effort and silently downgraded to static menus unless verbose logs are enabled.\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- Provider startup can partially degrade without a visible warning.\n- Operators may not realize external arg menus are disabled.\n- Debugging Slack command UX regressions becomes harder than necessary.\n\n## Suggested Direction\n\nWhen external arg-menu registration fails:\n\n- emit a visible warning, health event, or startup status entry\n- optionally expose the degraded mode through diagnostics/doctor output\n- keep the current fallback behavior so provider startup still succeeds\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- The fallback remains non-fatal.\n- Operators can tell when external arg menus were disabled.\n- The degraded-mode signal is visible without requiring verbose logs.\n",
